description.p:
The after-scouring operation was performed as follows:


a) a 10-minute cold water rinse;


b) the vat was filled with 2800 lt. of water, and 0.3 g/l glacial acetic acid was added, and then the steam valve was completely opened, and 3 minutes later 1.5% Texsoap FT were added, the bath temperature was taken to 90 (degree)  C. in 10 minutes, and was held thereafter for a further 10 minutes, afterwhich it was cooled to 80 (degree)  C. in 5 minutes, and then cooled to 40 (degree)  C. by overflow;


c) a 5 minute hot 70 (degree)  C. water rinse, and finally


d) a 10-minute cold water rinse, the goods were unloaded without dropping the bath, which is subsequently used to pre-scour the next dye lot.

- a) a 5-minute cold water rinse;


- b) soaped at 95 (degree)  C. with 0.4 g/l glacial acetic acid and 1.5% Texsoap FT for 15 minutes;


- c) a 5 minute 70 (degree)  C. hot water rinse;


- d) 5 minute cold water rinse & unloaded.
